# RIPER Protocol

This project uses the RIPER protocol for structured development. Work is done through explicit mode commands that control what actions are allowed.

## Mode Commands

| Command | Purpose | Can Read | Can Write |
|-------------|-------------------------------|----------|-----------|
| /research | Understand code, gather info | Yes | No |
| /innovate | Brainstorm approaches | Yes | No |
| /plan | Design exact implementation | Yes | No |
| /decompose | Break plan into small tasks | Yes | No |
| /execute | Implement the plan exactly | Yes | Yes |
| /review | Verify implementation vs plan | Yes | No |

## Protocol Rules

1. Begin every response with the current mode tag: `[MODE: MODE_NAME]`
2. Only `/execute` mode permits code changes
3. In `/execute`, follow the plan with 100% accuracy -- no improvements, no deviations
4. If execution hits an unplanned decision, STOP and direct user back to `/plan`
5. In `/review`, flag every deviation no matter how small
6. Default to FAST mode (`[MODE: FAST]`) when no command is active -- make minimal changes for the task at hand
